---
description: Widget rules for feature presentation widgets.
globs: lib/src/features/**/presentation/widgets/**/*.dart
alwaysApply: false
---

# Presentation Widget Rules

- Exactly one widget class per file. Never place two widget classes in the same file, even if one is private. If a widget owns meaningful structure or behavior, extract it into its own file instead of keeping it as a helper widget beside another widget.
- Widget names must clearly describe what the widget does.
- Every changeable UI value must come from constructor arguments or project tokens. Keep the API minimal: do not add parameters that are unused or not truly configurable.
- Never hardcode user-visible text, colors, asset paths, or other mutable design values.
- Use `context.l10n` for text, `context.colorScheme` for colors, and `context.assets` for assets.
- Input fields must not use `TextEditingController`. Input state lives in BLoC, widgets receive current value and validation from state, and report changes via callbacks.
- If spacing or corner radius already fits the design, use `AppSpacing` and `AppRadii` instead of raw numbers.
- Avoid unscoped magic numbers for layout and styling. Prefer theme tokens, named constants, or constructor parameters when a value may change.
- Avoid methods that return widgets. Prefer inline composition or a private widget class when extraction is justified.
- In vertically scrollable layouts, avoid fixed widths. In horizontally scrollable layouts, avoid fixed heights. Prefer `Padding`, `Expanded`, `Flexible`, alignment, and constraints.
- Use `MediaQuery.sizeOf(context)` for screen-relative sizing and `LayoutBuilder` for parent-relative sizing.
- Prefer `const` constructors and widgets whenever possible.

```dart
// ❌ BAD
class MyWidgetHeader extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyWidgetHeader({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => const Text('Title');
}
```

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
class ProfilePromoCard extends StatelessWidget {
  const ProfilePromoCard({
    super.key,
    required this.title,
    required this.description,
    required this.imageProvider,
    required this.onPressed,
  });
 
  final String title;
  final String description;
  final ImageProvider imageProvider;
  final VoidCallback onPressed;
}
```
